instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The twin architecture follows a microservice‑like distributed pattern orchestrated via an AMQP‐based message bus (RabbitMQ). The physical twin consists of a styrofoam housing with a heatbed, fan, two internal temperature sensors and an external sensor. A low‑level driver running on the Raspberry Pi directly reads the sensors and forwards the data to RabbitMQ; it also consumes heating/fan commands from RabbitMQ and publishes the current actuator states. The controller service, also on the Raspberry Pi, subscribes to the sensor streams, applies a relaxed bang‑bang logic (parameters LL, UL, H, C) to compute target heating signals, and commands the low‑level driver through RabbitMQ. Digital‑twin‑specific services include a real‑time dashboard that pulls data from a retained‑type time‑series database, a Kalman‑filter based anomaly detector that leverages the Model B dynamics, and a calibration service that triggers section 3.3 algorithms to re‑estimate model parameters. All services are coordinated by RabbitMQ ensuring loose coupling and enabling future scaling."
